Elkhorn Slough NERR, California After completing a 1.5-day training so that they can be their own tour Elkhorn Slough Environmental guides, teachers are able to schedule their classes for field trips and Education Program: Field have access to 5 miles of hiking trails, a visitor center with interpretive K-6th Experience exhibits, teaching lab with microscopes, picnic area, and a variety of kits for activities on the trails or in the classroom.
MERITO: Cielo al Mar (Sky to Sea); (Multicultural Education for Resource Issues Threatening Oceans) As part of the Monterey Bay National Marine Sanctuary's multicultural education plan, we work closely with a bilingual education specialist who is developing and testing bilingual 6th-8th curriculum about Elkhorn Slough wetlands and watersheds.
This is a pilot program currently being implemented at an after school program of a nearby middle school.
