North Inlet-Winyah NERR, South Carolina Estuary-Net is a high school water quality monitoring program first implemented by the NERRS several years ago; the program has lost funding, but was important to our educational programming and we have modified it somewhat and still use classroom, field/hands-on, and follow-up activities with several of our area high schools.
We 9th-12th provide teachers w/curriculum and sampling equipment, visit classrooms for presentations on water quality issues, teach students to use test equipment in the lab and in the field and they select sample sites to monitor and then submit their findings to us at our Reserve.
