Sapelo Island NERR, Georgia Visitors are introduced to the rich natural and cultural history of Sapelo Island, including elements of local maritime industry, the Gullah-Geechee community of Hog Hammock, as well as the agriculture and timber activities of the 1800s.
Instructors may also 5th-12th wish to include local Native American history and/or to highlight the influence of Spanish and French settlers on the island during the 15001700s.
Teachers call us to request an on-site field trip lasting from 1.5 to 5 hours.
These field trips include indoor and field experiences.
