The Bay Team
The Bay Team is an after-school science club for low income or underprivileged students in grades 4-6 who live in the neighborhood 4th-8th of Waquoit Bay National Estuarine Research Reserve.
Bay Team members learn about the water in the bay estuarine habitats, winds and tides, and the creatures that live along the shore and in the water.
